- AngularJS Supports the Following Storages.

    1.localStorage
    2.sessionStorage

- ngstorage is the predefined module , used to work with the storages.

- ngstorage module contains two predefined Objects.

    1.$localStorage

    2.$sessionStorage

        $localStorage used to work with the localStorage.
                (Explicitely we must delete)
        $sessionStorage used to work with the sessionStorage.
                (When ever we close the Broeser automatically data will be lost)


- we can save the data in the form of a "key & value" pairs.